-- Travelodge Takes $15.8 Million Emergency Loan, Times Reports
-- B y   H o w a r d   M u s t o e
-- 2012-02-12T11:52:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-12/travelodge-takes-15-8-million-emergency-loan-times-reports.html
Travelodge Ltd. took a 10 million
pound ($15.8 million) emergency bank loan ahead of talks with
its lenders, the Sunday Times of  London  reported, citing
unidentified bankers and people familiar with the matter.  The hotel operator, which runs 470 hotels in Britain,
Ireland and  Spain , has 850 million pounds of borrowings and paid
99 million pounds of interest last year, the newspaper said. A
Travelodge spokesman declined to comment when contacted by
Bloomberg News.  -- Editors: Alex Devine, Jonas Bergman  To contact the reporter on this story:
